It does. But I am trying make one more crucial point. Let me make it using an analogy.
 
Atleast in US, we have child-proof scissors that cut paper/cloth but do not cut the finger even if a child accidentally puts finger in it.
 
In an age when children did not need to use scissors and parents did scissors work for them, these kind of scissors weren't needed. Now, with parents being busy or otherwise unable to help, children need to use scissors for their homework sometimes. So the market came up with child-proof scissors that are safe and do not cut fingers.
 
Simialrly, remedies were done by trained experts (priests) in the past. As the priest class started to become weak and unable to help laymen, Nature is evolving things so that laymen are enabled and safely too.
 
*        *        *
 
In the old days, ruling kshatriya class contained very dharmik kings who were unselfish and used the power and authority vested in them to provide prosperity to their subjects and render selfless justice. As Kali yuga advanced and the kshatriya class became selfish, self-serving and incapable, Nature gave rise to an evolution and people became responsible for governing themselves. Kings who rule for their entire life are slowly fading away from the surface of earth and democracy is taking root everywhere, where kings change in every few years.
 
Similarly, priest class of old days contained genuine braahmanas who did sadhana, realized god and were selfless and used the energy they accumulated through sadhana to provide prosperity, material and spiritual, to people around them selflessly. As Kali yuga advances and the braahmana class becomes selfish, self-serving and incapable, Nature is giving rise to an evolution and people are responsible for their own remedies and sadhana for material prosperity and spiritual evolution.
 
But it is not so bad. Nature is very kind. Nature makes easy and safe tools available to laymen before its tells them "you're on your own".
 
*        *        *
 
People are suffering from terrible material problems now-a-days and also starving for good spiritual direction.
 
Based on old habits, they instinctively expect someone else to fix their problems. They think that getting a pooja or homam done by a priest for a couple of hours oneday or getting a "charged" yantra and rudraksha maalaa will magically cure their problems. Unfortunately, it is not so simple today. If there is a sadhaka who does enough sadhana and "charges" an object such as a yantra or a maalaa or an idol with that energy and gives it to you, you can indeed benefit from it. But gone are those days and gone are those people. Remember, you're on your own!
 
Forget special yantras, forget special maalaas, forget special idols, and forget rituals done by priests. Have faith, have confidence and do sadhana by yourself on a regular basis.
 
The most effective and safest sadhana to do by oneself is homam (fire ritual). Download the homam manuals (see site below) and try a homam on a regular basis.
 
Or pick a mantra and do japam with it mentally everyday for an hour or so, while sitting still with closed eyes and an erect back. If your knees hurt, sit on a chair or sofa comfortably, but keep the back straight and eyes closed.
 
*        *        *
 
There are many generic mantras (see my original mail at the bottom for a sample list) that are appliable to everybody and can solve ALL problems. For example, Vishnu sahasranaama stotra explicitly says it can solve ANY problem. Instead of looking for a "perfect mantra recommendation", you can pick a generic mantra like that and start sadhana. The key is faith and persistence.
 
If your kaarmik blockage is the size of a rock, small amount energy may be enough to move it away. If it is the size of a big boulder on the other hand, much more energy may be needed.
 
All that is in your hands is to do sadhana with faith and persistence. And, remember, no effort is ever wasted. Every effort bears a fruit of comparable size eventually.
 
Of course, you may be looking for a shortcut, but there is NONE. And sadhana is not so bad. Even before it solves your actual problem, the first thing sadhana does to you is: it gives you the courage to face the problem.
 
*        *        *
 
> Doing sadhana and selfless surrender to the supreme being
> is of course ideal, but not tenable in the current times
