That is what we are trying to do here..
 
*        *        *
 
Every mandala in RigVeda starts with hymns to Fire. Fire was worshipped by ancient people such as Zorostrains,  Vedic rishis and ancient Greco-Romans. Even progressive modern paths such as Buddhism and Arya Samaj accept fire worship. Fire is a living representation of divinity on earth and spending time worshipping god in fire has a magical and purifying impact on one's consciousness.
 
The proof of the pudding is in eating it. One can try homam every day or or every weekend for a few months and see for oneself what it does to one.
 
